FBIS4-15319 "drsov068_s_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-068 Daily Report 7 Apr 1994 Georgia Ministry Accuses Abkhazia of Resuming Hostilities Ministry Accuses Abkhazia of Resuming Hostilities LD0704131794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1214 GMT 7 Apr 94 LD0704131794 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tengis Pachkoria] [Text] Tbilisi April 7 TASS -- The Georgian Defence Ministry issued a statement today accusing separatist Abkhazia of resuming hostilities in the Kodor Gorge, high in the Caucasus mountains, on Wednesday. Despite a recent Moscow-brokered truce accord, Abkhazians have delivered an artillery strike on the village of Kvabchara, the press centre of the ministry said adding that the Georgian side abiding by the truce accord did not fire back.
